Nichelle Nichols, a trailblazer in the world of stage and screen, has passed away. She was known for her groundbreaking portrayal of Lt. Uhura in the original Star Trek series, becoming the first Black woman to have a major role on a primetime television show. Nichols's work helped redefine what was possible for Black Americans and women, breaking stereotypes and inspiring generations. She also collaborated with NASA to encourage people from all backgrounds to pursue scientific pursuits and reach for the stars. Her legacy as an inspiring artist will forever be remembered.